isCodeComplete(int) - Method in class decoder.IntermediateNode
Given a size checks if this node has number of children equal to the size parameter passed and checks if its children also have number of children equal to the size parameter passed, it returns false if check fails for any node, and if passes for every node, returns true.
isCodeComplete(int) - Method in class decoder.LeafNode
Returns true by default as no leaf nodes have children.
isCodeComplete(int) - Method in interface decoder.TreeNode
Given a size, check if all nodes in the tree have number of children equal to the size passed.
